fields.description: Our deepest fear is not that we are inadequate, it is that we are powerful beyond measure.
fields.author: Marianne Williamson

fields.description: Right now, your competition is training
fields.author: Unknown

fields.description: Be stronger than your excuses.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.description: What we face may look insurmountable. But I learned something from all those years of training and competing. I learned something from all those sets and reps when I didn’t think I could lift another ounce of weight. What I learned is that we are always stronger than we know.
fields.author: Arnold Schwarzenegger

fields.description: The battles that count aren’t the ones for gold medals. The struggles within yourself – the invisible, inevitable battles inside all of us – that’s where it’s at.
fields.author: Jesse Owens

fields.description: Don’t decrease the goal. Increase the effort.
fields.author: Tom Coleman

fields.description: The moment when you want to quit is the moment when you need to keep pushing.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.description: Don’t complain. Just work harder.
fields.author: Randy Pausch

fields.description: Only a man who knows what it is like to be defeated can reach down to the bottom of his soul and come up with the extra ounce of power it takes to win when the match is even.
fields.author: Muhammad Ali

fields.description: Success isn’t always about greatness. It’s about consistency. Consistent hard work gains success. Greatness will come.
fields.author: Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson

fields.description: Don’t stop until you’re proud.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.description: I am building a fire, and every day I train, I add more fuel.
fields.author: Mia Hamm

fields.description: You don’t get the ass you want by sitting on it
fields.author: Unknown

fields.description: Hustle for the muscle.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.description: One word: ‘fight.’ Anyone can do it when it feels good. When you’re hurting, that’s when it makes a difference, so you have to keep fighting
fields.author: Erin Cafaro

fields.description: If it is important to you, you will find a way. If not, you’ll find an excuse.
fields.author: Ryan Blair

fields.description: Strength does not come from winning. Your struggles develop your strengths. When you go through hardships and decide not to surrender, that is strength.
fields.author: Arnold Schwarzenegger

fields.description: I fear not the man who has practiced 10,000 kicks once, but I fear the man who has practiced one kick 10,000 times.
fields.author: Bruce Lee

fields.description: Physical fitness can neither be achieved by wishful thinking nor outright purchase.
fields.author: Joseph Pilates

fields.description: Isn’t it funny how day by day nothing changes, but when you look back, everything is different.
fields.author: Prince Caspian, by C.S. Lewis

fields.description: Surpassing my achievements feels incredible; I want to replicate that again and again.
fields.author: Katherine Reutter-Adamek

fields.description: The key is not the will to win. Everybody has that. It is the will to prepare to win that is important.
fields.author: Bobby Knight, in Knight: My Story

fields.description: Sticks and stones may break my bones but squats will make me badass.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.description: Doing the best at this moment puts you in the best place for the next moment.
fields.author: Oprah Winfrey

fields.description: I’ve never lost a game. I just ran out of time.
fields.author: Michael Jordan

fields.description: Take care of your body. It’s the only place you have to live.
fields.author: Jim Rohn

fields.description: In theory there is no difference between theory and practice. In practice there is.
fields.author: Yogi Berra

fields.description: It ain’t over ’till it’s over.
fields.author: Yogi Berra
